ING Vysya Said to Raise $117 Million in Sale to Institutional Investors

-- B y   R u t h   D a v i d
-- 
2011-06-15T04:25:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/ing-vysya-said-to-raise-117-million-in-sale-to-institutional-investors.html
ING Vysya Bank Ltd. (VYSB) , the Indian unit
of the biggest Dutch financial services company, raised 5.24
billion rupees ($117 million) selling shares to institutional
investors, according to two people with knowledge of the deal.  The bank sold 15.3 million shares at 342.09 rupees apiece
in the transaction that closed today, the people said, declining
to be named because the details aren’t public yet.  The share sale was about 2 times oversubscribed and
institutional investors including Wellington Financial LP and
DSP BlackRock Mutual Fund bought the shares, one of the people
said.  ING Groep NV (INGA)  owns 43.2 percent in Bangalore-based ING
Vysya, which has board approval to sell another 13.2 million
shares. ING will now buy shares via a preferential allotment to
retain its stake, the people said.  ING Vysya’s shares rose 1.8 percent to 346.90 rupees as of
9:34 a.m. local time. Enam Securities Pvt., IDFC Capital Ltd.
and  JM Financial Ltd. (JM)  are managing the share sale, a document
obtained by Bloomberg News yesterday showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
